cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DB 

This paper discusses the design of more efficient and flexible networks for big data, which involves networking and data management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the importance of intelligent networking and proposes a matching model for flow tables in SDN switches, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions the utilization rate and matching efficiency of the flow table, which could relate to cs.DC (Databases) and cs.DB (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
